<TITLE> Beheaded pathologist found </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narashingdi, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  The police recovered body of a pathologist of Narashingdi Sadar Hospital from the railway station in the town on Wednesday morning. Railway police said local people saw Sanjit Kumar Saha's body at Arsinagar outer signal area and informed the police about it. His sister Mitu Saha identified the body seeing the dress. Quoting family members, Narashingdi railway station master Maran Chandra Saha said Sanjit left his house immediately after taking supper and did not return on Tuesday night. A case was filed with Bhairab Police Station in this connection. District civil surgeon Dr Abdur Rashid, doctors, nurses and other colleagues of Sanjit went to the railway station to see the body. bdnews
